      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(onboarding): add browser Gemma setup assistant",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nInteractive local onboarding is currently terminal-only, which makes first-run setup difficult to explain and explore. This adds a browser-first onboarding surface backed by a small local Gemma 4 E2B model running through WebGPU, while keeping OpenClaw's existing setup wizard authoritative for credentials, configuration, plugin installs, and Gateway lifecycle.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\n- Adds a dedicated `/setup` browser surface launched by interactive local `openclaw onboard`.\n- Uses `@litert-lm/core@0.12.1` with same-origin bundled LiteRT WASM assets and a fixed Gemma 4 E2B web model URL.\n- Reuses the existing `wizard.start`, `wizard.next`, `wizard.status`, and `wizard.cancel` protocol.\n- Starts a short-lived loopback, sidecar-free Gateway for setup and persists redacted wizard checkpoints in the existing Task Flow registry.\n- Keeps explicit advanced/provider/import/reset/daemon flags on the canonical terminal wizard path.\n- Preserves `--non-interactive`, remote onboarding, and `--no-browser` behavior.\n\n## User Impact\n\n- Plain interactive local `openclaw onboard` opens the browser setup page when a browser can be launched.\n- Users can answer ordinary wizard steps in natural language or use structured controls.\n- Sensitive values are submitted directly to OpenClaw and appear only as masked chat markers; they are not passed through Gemma.\n- If WebGPU/model loading is unavailable, structured controls remain available.\n- If browser launch/setup fails, the CLI offers terminal onboarding.\n- Explicit advanced flags automatically use terminal onboarding to preserve exact semantics.\n\n## Evidence\n\nFocused proof:\n\n- `pnpm build`\n- `pnpm lint:core`\n- `pnpm check:import-cycles`\n- `pnpm check:docs`\n- `pnpm ui:i18n:check`\n- `pnpm test src/gateway/credentials.test.ts src/gateway/gateway.test.ts src/gateway/control-ui-csp.test.ts src/gateway/server-runtime-config.test.ts src/cli/program/register.onboard.test.ts src/commands/onboard-interactive.test.ts src/wizard/session.test.ts ui/src/setup/model.test.ts ui/src/setup/setup-app.test.ts`\n- Browser visual proof at desktop and mobile viewports under `.artifacts/control-ui-e2e/browser-onboarding/`.\n- Isolated runtime smoke verified authenticated `/setup`, explicit setup-route CSP, and same-origin LiteRT WASM assets.\n- Fresh autoreview: clean, no accepted/actionable findings.\n\nChanged-check delegation is currently unavailable in this environment: Blacksmith CLI is missing, Azure is not logged in, and direct AWS Crabbox credentials are unavailable. The local equivalent checks above pass.\n\n## VM Test Instructions\n\n1. Start from a clean VM with an empty OpenClaw state directory.\n2. Run interactive `openclaw onboard`.\n3. Confirm the browser setup page opens and the Gemma E2B model loads from the local browser path.\n4. Exercise natural-language selection plus structured controls, including one sensitive credential field.\n5. Verify the Gateway, workspace, daemon, health, and selected channel/plugin setup complete normally.\n6. Close/reopen the setup tab and verify the heartbeat/watchdog behavior does not leave the CLI or temporary Gateway stranded.\n7. Repeat with WebGPU unavailable and confirm the structured/terminal fallback.\n8. Verify `openclaw onboard --no-browser`, explicit advanced flags, `--non-interactive`, and remote onboarding remain on their existing paths.\n\nThis is intentionally a draft PR pending VM proof of the real Gemma download/inference path and full first-run setup behavior.",
